1.	Share /k8svol from nfs server
2.	Create a nfs based pv (nfsvol) of 2 GB
3.	Bind a pvc (nfspvc) with ReadWriteMany access mode and 2GiB 
4.	Configure a pod to claim the volume. Download below YAML file and modify accordingly.
5.	Configure a cluster on Google cloud with default options
6.	Provision ssd based pv named as “fast-disk”
7.	Bind a PVC (named as – gcp-pvc) from “fast-disk” of size 5GB with “ReadWriteOnce” access mode.
8.	Configure a deployment using gcp-pvc as volume.
